00:37:13.880 --> 00:37:16.120
but could you speak to that?

00:37:16.120 --> 00:37:17.750
ROHAN DIXIT: Sure.

00:37:17.750 --> 00:37:19.770
That's something I
think about a lot.

00:37:19.770 --> 00:37:21.665
The amount of sensory
input we have on a day

00:37:21.665 --> 00:37:24.320
to day basis in terms of
distractions is out of control.

00:37:24.320 --> 00:37:28.240
Like it's probably never been
seen in human history before.

00:37:28.240 --> 00:37:31.240
I mean checking your
email, Twitter, Facebook.

00:37:31.240 --> 00:37:33.430
There's just
constant distraction.

00:37:33.430 --> 00:37:37.210
And to a degree that's being
facilitated by technology.

00:37:37.210 --> 00:37:40.960
So it's a little bit ironic
to use that same technology

00:37:40.960 --> 00:37:45.460
kind of approach to get
you out of that loop.

00:37:45.460 --> 00:37:47.780
Perhaps that's the way to do it.

00:37:47.780 --> 00:37:50.370
I think in years
past probably people

00:37:50.370 --> 00:37:52.500
were able to sustain
their attention

00:37:52.500 --> 00:37:54.990
for longer periods of time.

00:37:54.990 --> 00:37:57.580
And that's probably a factor
of having less input and less

00:37:57.580 --> 00:37:59.490
distraction in general.

00:37:59.490 --> 00:38:01.840
So I do feel that
technology now has a role

00:38:01.840 --> 00:38:04.800
to play in bringing us back to
the ability to pay attention,

00:38:04.800 --> 00:38:07.386
not only to things around
us in terms of focus,

00:38:07.386 --> 00:38:09.010
but also to pay
attention to ourselves.

00:38:09.010 --> 00:38:10.530
And I think that's where a
lot of self growth happens.

00:38:10.530 --> 00:38:12.530
That's what I'm
really interested in

00:38:12.530 --> 00:38:16.970
because that's where a lot of my
growth personally has happened.

00:38:16.970 --> 00:38:18.940
AUDIENCE: So you
mentioned biofeedback.

00:38:18.940 --> 00:38:24.820
Have you given any thought
